## Redirect Context and Categorization  

This redirect exists in that special digital purgatory reserved for pages that got [renamed](/Wikipedia:Renaming) but still need to pretend they're useful. The [categories](/Wikipedia:Categorizing_redirects) slapped onto it serve two purposes:  

### [From a page move](/Category:Redirects_from_moves)  
- Translation: *"We changed the sign on the door but left the rotting furniture inside."*  
- This category hoards redirects created when someone decided the original page title wasn't depressing enough. It prevents the internet from collapsing into a black hole of [broken links](/Link_rot) – because nothing terrifies editors more than users actually finding what they search for.  
- Fun fact: The [protection levels](/Wikipedia:Protection_policy) on these redirects often range from "lightly guarded" to "fortress of solitude," depending on how many editors have rage-quit over naming disputes.  

### [From a longer title](/Category:Redirects_from_long_names)  
